Generated Narrative: ImplementationGuide example.fhir.ph.roadsafety

Language: en

PHRoadSafetyIG

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

https://build.fhir.org/ig/UPM-NTHC/PH-RoadSafetyIG/ImplementationGuide/example.fhir.ph.roadsafety

FHIR IG for road safety and health information in the Philippines

name: PHRoadSafetyIG
title: DRAFT PH Road Safety Implementation Guide
publisher: UP Manila - National Institutes of Health - National Telehealth Center

contact.name: UP Manila - National Institutes of Health - National Telehealth Center

description: FHIR IG for road safety and health information in the Philippines

extension.valueMarkdown: Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on HL7 Terminology
Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on the HL7 Extension Pack

resource.name: Accident Scene Location
resource.description: Road traffic accident scene for the encounter.

resource.name: Activity ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Example ValueSet for Activity at time of incident

resource.name: Age
resource.description: Patient age, derived from birthDate. Not intended for direct data entry.

resource.name: Age Units ValueSet
resource.description: Allowed units for Patient Age when Date of Birth is not available.

resource.name: All Road Safety Procedure Codes
resource.description: Combines medical interventions, first aid, and psychosocial procedures.

resource.name: Cause of Crash File Type ValueSet
resource.description: Allowed file types for documents describing the cause of a road crash.

resource.name: Cause of Road Crash
resource.description: Defines codes representing the external causes of road traffic crashes

resource.name: Cause of Road Crash Incident
resource.description: Cause or contributing factor of the road crash.

resource.name: City General Hospital
resource.description: Receiving medical facility for the road safety encounter.

resource.name: City General Hospital - Emergency Department
resource.description: ED Location involved in the encounter.

resource.name: Collision Type ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Types of collision in road traffic incidents

resource.name: Emergency Department Availability
resource.description: Indicates if the emergency department is currently accepting patients.

resource.name: Example Hospital Organization
resource.description: Hospital submitting the road safety patient report.

resource.name: External Cause Detail
resource.description: Additional detail for external cause (e.g., specify animal/insect, weapon, burn type).

resource.name: External Cause ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Illustrative set of codes representing external causes of injury.

resource.name: First Aid Codes
resource.description: Allowed values for first aid performed.

resource.name: First Aid Given
resource.description: Indicates whether first aid was provided to the patient.

resource.name: Hospital / EMS Category
resource.description: Categories for hospitals relevant to EMS referral.

resource.name: Hospital Available
resource.description: Represents a hospital available for EMS referral, linked to its location.

resource.name: Hospital Case Number System
resource.description: Unique identifier assigned to each hospital case.

resource.name: Hospital Patient ID No.
resource.description: The permanent and unique number issued by hospitals to individual patients and their dependents.

resource.name: Incident Number System
resource.description: Unique identifier assigned to each incident.

resource.name: Injury Observation
resource.description:
It is intended to support documentation of external causes, nature and extent of injuries, 
vital signs, Glasgow Coma Scale, and other clinical or scene observations related to road traffic incidents.

resource.name: MDS Logical Model to FHIR Mapping
resource.description: Maps elements from the MDSRoadSafety logical model to target FHIR R4 resources.

resource.name: Medical Intervention Procedure Codes
resource.description: Procedure codes representing medical interventions.

resource.name: Mode of Transport ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Sample ValueSet capturing transport modes.

resource.name: National Health Facility Registry ID
resource.description: The permanent and unique number issued by PhilHealth to individual members and to each and every dependent.

resource.name: Nature of Injury ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Demonstration ValueSet capturing the nature of injury.

resource.name: Outcome ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Example ValueSet capturing possible outcomes.

resource.name: Party at Fault
resource.description: Identifies the party considered at fault in the road crash.

resource.name: Party at Fault
resource.description: ValueSet indicating the party at fault in an incident.

resource.name: Patient - Jose Dela Cruz
resource.description: Road crash patient referenced by the ServiceRequest example.

resource.name: patient-road-safety-ex
resource.description: Example patient involved in a road traffic crash, aligned to the RoadSafetyProfile.

resource.name: PH Core Occupation (Stub)
resource.description: Temporary local copy of PH Core Occupation extension for Road Safety testing

resource.name: Place of Occurrence ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Example ValueSet capturing places of occurrence.

resource.name: Practitioner - Ana Cruz
resource.description: Team Leader in the Road Safety Encounter (Dr. Ana Cruz leads the medical response team).

resource.name: Practitioner - John Lee
resource.description: Assistant in the Road Safety Encounter (Nurse John Lee assists the treatment and transport officers).

resource.name: Practitioner - Lisa Tan
resource.description: Transport Officer in the Road Safety Encounter (Dr. Lisa Tan is responsible for patient transfer and transport decisions).

resource.name: Practitioner - Maria Santos
resource.description: Received By in the Road Safety Encounter (Clerk Maria Santos logs the patientâ€™s arrival at the receiving facility).

resource.name: Practitioner - Mark Reyes
resource.description: Treatment Officer in the Road Safety Encounter (Dr. Mark Reyes provides primary patient treatment).

resource.name: Psychosocial Procedure Codes
resource.description: Codes representing psychosocial support interventions.

resource.name: Refusal to Admit Service Request
resource.description: Profile for recording refusal to admit a patient.

resource.name: Refusal to Admit Service Request Example
resource.description: This example records a refusal to admit a road crash patient during a Road Safety Encounter, including the hospital that refused admission and the physician involved.

resource.name: Report Form Received
resource.description: Whether the report form was received as digital or physical.

resource.name: Report Form Received
resource.description: ValueSet indicating whether a report form has been received.

resource.name: Road Network File Type
resource.description: Permitted file types for detailed road network shapefiles or GIS documents.

resource.name: Road Network File Type
resource.description: Allowed file types for detailed road network shapefiles or GIS data.

resource.name: Road Network Shape File
resource.description: Metadata reference to detailed road network shapefile related to the incident.

resource.name: Road Safety AllergyIntolerance
resource.description: Profile for recording allergy or intolerance information in the Philippine Road Safety IG.

resource.name: Road Safety Claim
resource.description: A Claim profile for PH Road Safety IG requiring total.

resource.name: Road Safety Condition
resource.description: A Condition for the Safety of the Roads in the Philippines.

resource.name: Road Safety Document Reference
resource.description: A profile to capture documents related to road safety incidents in the Philippine context.

resource.name: Road Safety Encounter
resource.description: Encounter profile for road safety reporting (hospital case no, incident no, transport details, disposition, etc.)

resource.name: Road Safety Encounter Example
resource.description: Example of a road safety hospital encounter with identifiers, participants, and disposition.

resource.name: Road Safety MedicationStatement
resource.description: A profile representing a patient's current medication statement for the Philippine health context.

resource.name: Road Safety Minimum Dataset (MDS) Logical Model
resource.description: Abstract, sectioned logical model for the PH Road Safety MDS covering incident, patient, encounter, clinical, vitals, injuries, evidence/documents, workflow, and finance. Elements mirror the CSV rows; mappings point to target FHIR elements for subsequent profiling.

resource.name: Road Safety Patient
resource.description: A profile for Road Safety resource specific to Philippine context.

resource.name: Road Safety Patient Example - Age Only
resource.description: Example of a patient where only age is known.

resource.name: Road Safety Patient Example - Elderly
resource.description: Example of an elderly patient with approximate age.

resource.name: Road Safety Patient Example - Infant Age
resource.description: Example of a pediatric patient with age in months.

resource.name: Road Safety Patient Example - With Two Addresses
resource.description: A patient with both permanent and temporary addresses.

resource.name: Road Safety Procedure
resource.description:
Procedure profile for road safety and injury surveillance.
- Captures interventions performed on the patient.
- Supplies used during the procedure.
- Coordination with receiving hospital if applicable.

resource.name: Road Safety Questionnaire
resource.description: A profile on Questionnaire to capture repeating Vital Signs data (Respiratory Rate, Pulse, Blood Pressure, Temperature, LOC).

resource.name: Road Safety Task
resource.description: A profile for tasks related to road safety, tracking report forms and delays.

resource.name: Road Safety Task Example
resource.description: Example of a road safety task to track report form receipt and delays.

resource.name: Road Safety Task Status
resource.description: ValueSet for Task.status using custom Road Safety codes.

resource.name: Road Safety Task Status Codes
resource.description: Custom codes for Task.status specific to Road Safety reporting.

resource.name: Supplies Used
resource.description: Records any devices or medications used during the procedure.

resource.name: Traffic Incident Management
resource.description: Documentation or status of traffic incident management.

resource.name: Transport Coordination
resource.description: Indicates if transport to receiving hospital was coordinated.

resource.name: Transport Coordination Codes
resource.description: Standard codes for documenting transport coordination.

resource.name: Transport Details
resource.description: Details about mode of transport, vehicles involved, positions.

resource.name: Triage Priority ValueSet (example)
resource.description: Example ValueSet capturing triage priorities.

resource.name: UP Philippine General Hospital (UP-PGH)
resource.description: Hospital referenced in the ServiceRequest example (refused admission).

resource.name: ValueSet for Vehicle Used
resource.description: Vehicle types allowed for Road Safety Encounter

resource.name: Vehicle Condition
resource.description: Condition of the vehicle involved in the incident.

resource.name: Vehicle Condition
resource.description: ValueSet indicating the condition of a vehicle.

resource.name: Vehicle Types
resource.description: A code system for different types of vehicles used in road safety encounters.

resource.name: Vehicle Used
resource.description: The type of vehicle used by the patient or involved in the encounter.

resource.name: Vital Signs Questionnaire
resource.description: Example Questionnaire instance to capture repeating sets of Vital Signs.

resource.name: Vital Signs QuestionnaireResponse Example
resource.description: Example response to the Vital Signs Questionnaire with sample measurements.
